Partition Level Checksum (Best Practice)
Since your table is partitioned by report_date, validate per partition.
Old table:
SQL
Copy code
SELECT
report_date,
CHECKSUM_AGG(BINARY_CHECKSUM(*)) checksum_value
FROM dbo.cff_report
GROUP BY report_date
New table:
SQL
Copy code
SELECT
report_date,
CHECKSUM_AGG(BINARY_CHECKSUM(*)) checksum_value
FROM dbo.cff_report_new
GROUP BY report_date
Example output
Plain text
Copy code
report_date   checksum
2024-01-01    8932121
2024-02-01    9812231
Both tables must match.
Why BINARY_CHECKSUM is Used
BINARY_CHECKSUM calculates checksum row by row.
Example:
SQL
Copy code
SELECT BINARY_CHECKSUM(*)
FROM dbo.cff_report
Result:
Plain text
Copy code
Row1 → 1231
Row2 → 8912
Row3 → 3321
Then
SQL
Copy code
CHECKSUM_AGG
combines them into one number.
